5|$|Beginning in the 2004–05 NHL season, the Canadiens adopted Youppi! {{as their}} {{official}} mascot, the first costumed mascot in their long history. Youppi was the longtime mascot for <b>the</b> <b>Montreal</b> <b>Expos</b> baseball team, but was {{dropped from the}} franchise when they moved to Washington, D.C. in 2004 and became the Washington Nationals. With the switch, Youppi became the first mascot in professional sports to switch leagues.|$|E
